<span id="freeTextContainer5585329653545328912">(Note: I have autism)<br/><br/>I have to admit, I was on the verge of crying at some parts<br/><br/>because this book is everything I&apos;ve wanted to tell the world but didn&apos;t know how<br/><br/>it made me understand myself a bit better, because like the author, I am not always sure why I do the things I do<br/><br/>It is one of those books I want as many as people as possible to read, to try and understand people with autism a bit better, and get rid of misconceptions.<br/></span>
  <span id="freeText5585329653545328912" style="display:none">(Note: I have autism)<br /><br />I have to admit, I was on the verge of crying at some parts<br /><br />because this book is everything I've wanted to tell the world but didn't know how<br /><br />it made me understand myself a bit better, because like the author, I am not always sure why I do the things I do<br /><br />It is one of those books I want as many as people as possible to read, to try and understand people with autism a bit better, and get rid of misconceptions.<br /></span>
