    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_3662081809" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3662081809" />
    <a title="❀ Rose ❀" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/58480863-rose"><img alt="❀ Rose ❀" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1631129328p2/58480863.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3662081809?book_show_action=true">Dec 18, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="❀ Rose ❀" class="user" itemprop="url" name="❀ Rose ❀" href="/user/show/58480863-rose">❀ Rose ❀</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3662081809" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer915328212442948597"><i><b>“True compassion is about not bruising the other person’s self-respect.” </b> </i><br/><br/>What a beautiful enlightening read. It both breaks your heart and fills it with the most mushy and beautiful feelings ever. I highly recommend it as it is a very important read. It also gives you an insight into what goes on in the brain of people who have autism. <br/><br/>Highly recommend: it’s also very very short so its definitely a quick read!</span>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

